#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{2}\n"
"You may modify the rules to increase or decrease difficulty, change how the game flows, or adjust its pacing.\n"
"These are suggestions from the game developers.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\bigskip\n"
"\\subheader{Chaos Cards}\n"
"Whenever you are about to discard a card, Remove that card instead.\n"
"Then, take the top card from the corresponding Deck and place it in your discard pile.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Note:} Statistic and Specialty cards are still discarded normally.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:16
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Even if you use a \\wikilink{statistics/knowledge}{Knowledge card} to return a Spell to your hand, the Spell is still removed, and you receive a new one from the top of the Spell Deck instead.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\bigskip\n"
"\\subheader{Neutral Army}\n"
"When you use a Population token to \\textbf{recruit} units, instead of \\textbf{recruiting} them normally, for every Dwelling you have, draw 2 corresponding Neutral Unit cards.\n"
"You can \\textbf{recruit} any number of these units if you \\svg{pay} their \\svg{recruit} costs.\n"
"Discard all units that were not recruited.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Note:} This variant is recommended only when there are no Heroes with unit-oriented Special Abilities in the game.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:30
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\begin{center}\n"
#| "  \\includegraphics[width=\\linewidth]{\\art/dendroid.jpg}\n"
#| "\\end{center}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"\\vspace*{\\fill}\n"
"\\begin{center}\n"
"  \\transparent{0.2}\\includegraphics[width=0.5\\linewidth]{\\art/leprechaun.png}\n"
"\\end{center}\n"
"\\vspace*{\\fill}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\begin{center}\n"
"  \\includegraphics[width=\\linewidth]{\\art/dendroid.jpg}\n"
"\\end{center}\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\columnbreak\n"
"\\subheader{Draft Start}\n"
"This rule allows you to modify your starting Deck by drafting its contents during the game’s setup.\n"
"After choosing your Heroes, instead of creating their normal starting Decks, follow the steps below.\n"
"For each chosen Hero, take their Starting Ability card from the Ability Deck and their Level I Specialty card, and set them aside.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Shuffle the Artifact, Ability, and Spell Decks separately.\n"
"Each player draws the top 2 cards from each of these Decks and chooses one to keep.\n"
"Then, each player passes the remaining 5 cards to the player on their left.\n"
"Repeat this step until all of the cards have been taken.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When that happens, the players -- once again -- draw the top 2 cards from the three Decks, choose one to keep, and pass the remaining five to the next player, but this time to the one on their right.\n"
"Repeat the step until every player has a Deck totaling 12 cards drafted this way.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now, based on the icons shown on their Hero Board, each player adds the corresponding Statistic cards to their Deck.\n"
"At this point, a Might Hero's Deck should consist of 18 cards, and a Magic Hero's Deck of 17 cards.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each player selects 7 cards from their Deck (discarding the rest) and adds them to the two cards they set aside at the beginning.\n"
"Now, every player has their drafted Deck of 9 cards ready.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Note:} This variant is recommended for 3+ players.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:56
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\\pagetarget{Artifact}{Artifact} Cards"
msgid ""
"\\columnbreak\n"
"\\pagetarget{Split Artifact and Spell Decks}{\\subheader{Split Artifact and Spell Decks}}\n"
"\\index{Split Decks}\n"
"\n"
msgstr "Cartes d'\\pagetarget{Artifact}{Artefact}"

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:58
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Note:} Split Decks are often used in \\pagelink{Tournament Mode}{Tournament Mode}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:62
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"During Setup, split Artifact cards by \\pagelink{Artifact}{their level} into 3 separate Decks: Minor, Major and Relic.  % no-check-caps\n"
"Afterwards, split the Spell Deck into 2 separate Decks for \\pagelink{Schools of Magic}{Basic and Expert Spells}.\n"
"Discard the top card of each of the five Decks to form their Discard Pile.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each time you gain an Artifact card or a Spell card \\textbf{from visiting a Map Location}, perform a Search (X) action or draw a card from one of the available Decks depending on your Hero's position on the Map, according to the table below.\n"
"If several Decks are available, choose one.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\begin{table}[H]\n"
"\\hommtable{15}{\n"
"  \\centering\n"
"  \\medskip\n"
"  \\textbf{Deck availability}\\\\\n"
"  \\bigskip\n"
"  \\begin{tabularx}{0.95\\linewidth}{>{\\hsize=0.25\\hsize\\linewidth=\\hsize}X\n"
"    >{\\hsize=0.34\\hsize\\linewidth=\\hsize}X\n"
"    >{\\hsize=0.32\\hsize\\linewidth=\\hsize}X\n"
"  }\n"
"    \\darkcell[1.2]{Hero's\\\\ Position} & \\darkcell[1.2]{Artifact\\\\ Decks} & \\darkcell[1.2]{Spell\\\\ Decks} \\\\\n"
"    \\darkcell[1.2]{Tiles I, II--III} &\n"
"    \\lightcell[1.2]{Minor} &\n"
"    \\lightcell[1.2]{Basic} \\\\\n"
"    \\darkcell[1.2]{Tiles IV--V} &\n"
"    \\lightcell[1.2]{Minor\\\\ Major} &\n"
"    \\lightcell[1.2]{Basic\\\\ Expert} \\\\\n"
"    \\darkcell[1.6]{Tiles VI--VII} &\n"
"    \\lightcell[1.6]{Minor\\\\ Major\\\\ Relic} &\n"
"    \\lightcell[1.6]{Basic\\\\ Expert} \\\\\n"
"  \\end{tabularx}\n"
"}\n"
"\\end{table}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:92
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you gain an Artifact or a Spell \\textbf{outside of a Map Location} (e.g. by buying a Spell in a Mage Guild), \\textbf{only your Main Hero's position} is relevant for choosing from the available Decks.\n"
"% clarification: https://discord.com/channels/740870068178649108/897475192677355560/1201813535857057822 Or  https://discord.com/channels/740870068178649108/897475192677355560/1201802322624122930\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\vspace*{\\fill}\n"
"\\columnbreak\n"
"\\subheader{Gold Pool}\n"
"This alternative rule for building and managing your army changes the dynamics of multiplayer clash games, improving the experience, particularly in games with an odd number of players.\n"
"By mitigating the impact of casualties, it gives early combatants a fair chance against players with fresh armies and denies them an easy win.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:102
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Your pool of resources is now called the Unspent Pool.\n"
"When you use the Population token to \\textbf{recruit} or \\textbf{reinforce}, instead of placing the \\svg{gold} and \\svg{valuables} from your Unspent Pool back in the box, place the resources in a separate pile near your Unit Deck -- this will be your Reserved Pool.\n"
"The resources from the Reserved Pool cannot be used.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:106
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The next time you use your Population token to expand your army, you will be able to freely change your recruited units, meaning that you can not only buy new units, but also sell the ones you have.\n"
"When you sell a unit or when it perishes, simply return its costs -- both in \\svg{gold} and \\svg{valuables} -- from your Reserved Pool to your Unspent Pool.\n"
"You can \\textbf{recruit} and \\textbf{reinforce} as many units as you can afford.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Whenever your unit is flipped from the ``Pack'' side to the ``Few'' side, you regain the \\svg{reinforce}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/variants.tex:111
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Whenever you use a card that reduces a unit's \\textbf{recruitment} or \\textbf{reinforcement} costs, keep it with the unit's card to remind you how much \\svg{gold} and \\svg{valuables} you will regain when the unit perishes or when it is sold (or when it is flipped to the ``Few'' side, if you used the card to pay the \\svg{reinforce}).\n"
"When this happens, return the ``discount card'' to your hand."
msgstr ""

